HEADWORD: Prender
<hw>Pren"der</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>prendre</ets> to take, fr. L. <ets>prehendere</ets> to take.]</ety>
<fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The power or right of taking a thing before it is
offered.</def> <rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

